</country></address></addressbook></inventor><inventor sequence="03" designation="us-only"><addressbook><last-name>Lopez</last-name><first-name>Manolo</first-name><address><city>Milano</city><country>IT</country></address></addressbook></inventor></inventors></us-parties><pct-or-regional-filing-data><document-id><country>WO</country><doc-number>PCT/EP2010/007982</doc-number><kind>00</kind><date>20101230</date></document-id><us-371c124-date><date>20130920</date></us-371c124-date></pct-or-regional-filing-data></us-bibliographic-data-application><abstract id="abstract"><p id="p-0001" num="0000">A method of locating incipient faults that generate partial discharges in an AC power distribution system includes detecting at least one spike in a PD pattern generated by such system; getting the voltage wave of the AC power in the system; detecting a phase of such spike with respect to the voltage of the AC power; and locating an incipient fault where such phase is below a predetermined threshold. An apparatus includes at least one sensor of electrical pulses, means for getting a synchronism signal with a power supply of the power distribution system, and modules adapted to carry out the method.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>